history.content:
I haven't taken 168, but 188 is regarded as one of the lightest workload classes. There are homework questions on edx and 5 projects where you basically translate psuedocode given into slides into python.

Edit by someone who has taken both: For me the 168 projects and homeworks were more involved then the 188 counter parts. Both were much less then other upper divs like 170/162. That being said the 188 midterms and exams were more difficult then 168. In general both classes are fairly light, and the material is pretty different so I'd imagine the one you have more interest in the material would be easier, so I'd go for that one.
